09/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Political leaders held a working dinner Thursday (October 8th) with senior EU and US officials, ahead of formal discussions Friday about the stalemate that has blocked reforms for months.
Republika Srpska Prime Minister Milorad Dodik says the talks, at the Butmir military base near Sarajevo, focused on state property, possible constitutional changes, meeting conditions for closing the Office of the High Representative and criteria for visa liberalisation.
Swedish Foreign Minister Carl Bildt, whose country currently holds the rotating EU presidency, US Deputy Secretary of State James Steinberg and EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn participated.
According to local media, no agreement was reached, but none of the proposed options were rejected Another meeting is scheduled for October 20th.
(Fena, Srna, Dnevni Avaz, RTRS, AFP, BBC - 08/10/09)
